HEADWORD: Croze
<hw>Croze</hw> <pr>(kr?z)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Cross</er>,
and <er>Crosier</er>.]</ety> <def>A cooper's tool for making the grooves
for the heads of casks, etc.; also, the groove itself.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

